Chet, Andy, Tom, and the others who have voiced comment and opinion re me.  Let's stop the personal hits.  Not that I am on any higher or lower moral grounds, or that protestors are hot and you are not, but I think we are all doing two things the designers of this site were not ready for. (1). That emotions and anger and unresolved issues (even for shrinks) still run deep, and lead to accusations and personalizations that really do distract from whatever the designers wanted here.  (I guess raw emotions about blood and death don't fit into designer sites), but more importantly, (2) I don't want to be an issue (i.e. ME), I did not intend to accuse personally, or to demean anyone personally, but it seems that some of you have trouble seperating the issues from the personality, and I do not want this to be the B.S.'s Post Site.(pro or con). I know I am not the most subtle at times.<br><br>
Nam clearly remains a HOT issue, and one that needs to be talked about, expressed, yelled, etc., but this is not about any one individual, be it me or tanker or anon. I am guilty as most, better than some, worse than others, but equally as emotionally changed forever by that little card that I used to carry in my wallet, called a draft card. <br><br>
I will give this a rest for awhile, so that my name may ride off into the moral highground - sunset  (that's a joke folks). Maybe a touch of humor is something this sites needs too. <br><br>
doc <br><br>

